Fourth Department,

May, 1945.

(May 2, 1945.) County of Monroe, Plaintiff, v. County of Ontario, Defendant.

Submitted controversy dismissed, without costs and without prejudice, on the ground that the facts stipulated are insufficient upon which to make a determination. All concur. (Submission of controversy in an action to compel reimbursement for money expended for support of poor persons.) Present — Taylor, P. J., Dowling, McCurn, Larkin and Love, JJ.
